<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4407&amp;p=49561#p49561"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">wildonrio wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />He says he knows 6502<br /></div><br />Knowing 6502 and knowing how to make a game are very different things. If I had to pick someone that only knew one of those things, I'd pick the one that has programmed a game (or at least confidently knows he can) than the one that knows just 6502. The 6502 is very simple, and there are tons of references about it, any competent programmer will pick up on it quickly. The PPU is another big issue. Understanding how it works is also much more important than knowing 6502.<br /><br />I'm not saying the person you found knows or doesn't know things, I'm just expressing my opinions on what the priorities are.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Fri Aug 07, 2009 6:38 pm</p><hr />
